description:
**Tectonic is actively seeking a Receptionist to work within our Corporate Office located in Mountainville, NY to work 2-3 days per work week from 7:45 AM – 4:45 PM.**
**ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS**
* Phone reception using the Microsoft TEAMs system;
* Maintaining conference room calendars using Microsoft Outlook;
* Daily attendance tracking and screening visitors;
* Daily trip to the post office (one mile away) to drop off, pick up, and distribute Corporate mail;
* Preparing of mailings and shipments, and distribution of packages throughout the day;
* Basic data entry, scanning and copying documents as needed;
* Sanitizing of Corporate lobby and maintaining a neat and professional space;
* Assist HR Department with Corporate travel on an as needed basis;
* All other related tasks as needed to ensure the smooth functioning of the Corporate office.

**QUALIFICATIONS**
* 1 years of related administrative experience, preferably in a professional office environment and a HS Diploma/Equivalent;
* Must possess functional computer skills, especially in Microsoft Office Suite;
* Effective interpersonal and communication skills, both verbal and written, with the ability to act as a resource for and work effectively with diverse groups of people at various levels within a professional organization;
* Good sense and sound judgement in practical matters, with the ability to maintain confidentiality;
* Ability to multi-task in a professional atmosphere, independently or in a team environment;
* Must possess a valid, clean driver’s license and personal vehicle.

**PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS**
In order to perform the essential functions of this position, the candidate must be able to constantly assume a stationary position, and must handle and/or feel documents, materials, and/or equipment to perform necessary tasks, sometimes repetitively. The candidate must be able to occasionally maneuver within the office to access file cabinets, office machinery, etc., and may exert up to 15 lbs. of force occasionally. Constantly, they must be able to receive and convey detailed or important information with others via the Corporate e-mail system, telephone system, and in person.
The physical demands described above are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
**PAY RANGE**
*Tectonic’s goal is to compensate employees fairly and equitable across all positions Companywide. Our advertised pay ranges are representative of our good faith effort to provide a reasonable anticipated salary range. The offered pay may be outside of the provided salary range based upon the selected candidate’s work location, experience, education, certifications, and capabilities compared to the advertised position.*
Pay Range: $16.00 - $18.00 / hour
***We are an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer, and highly encourage resumes from all interested parties including women, minorities, veterans and persons with disabilities. All qualified applicants will be afforded equal employment opportunities without discrimination on the basis of race, creed, color, national origin, sex, age, disability, marital status, or any other protected class. Tectonic participates in the USCIS E-Verify Program to verify that all new hires are authorized to work in the United States.***

The Nutrition & Health Center is searching for a Clinical Nutritionist (per diem) for the office in Elizabeth, NJ to work on as-needed basis.

Responsibilities:

Provide nutrition services and medical nutrition therapy integrated with the patient's medical goals under the supervision of RDN;

Evaluate, interpret, monitor, and document the nutritional status and nutritional needs of patients using established standards of care and practice guidelines;

Identify and provide age-specific nutrition counseling to meet the cultural needs of the patients and their families;

Create notes, and keep proper charts of patient's visits and progress using EMR systems;

Utilize clinical software programs to facilitate nutrition therapy (FFQ Nutritionist Pro, bioimpedance body composition test, resting metabolic rate test, etc.);

Provide the information for each patient to perform necessary coding, billing, and EMR services;

Scheduling and attending meetings out of the office, if necessary;

Coordinate with local healthcare providers;

Maintain RDN status and current credentials with medical insurance companies, and have valid personal malpractice insurance;

Any other tasks and responsibilities the Employer deems appropriate and which are consistent with the RD position within this office.

Qualifications:

Bachelor's Degree;

Clinical nutritionist license/certificate;

Fluent Spanish and English are a MUST;

Fluency in Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, Access, etc.

Job Types: Part-time or per diem.

Job Type: Part-time

Pay: $26.00 - $28.00 per hour

Expected hours: 20 – 40 per week

Benefits:

* Flexible schedule

Medical Specialty:

* Bariatrics
* Dietetics
* Pediatrics

Schedule:

* Monday to Friday
* Weekends as needed

Education:

* Bachelor's (Required)

Experience:

* clinical nutritionist: 2 years (Required)

Work Location: In person
